1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,209
Ever notice how an enthusiastic salesperson in a department store gets you, the customer, more excited about the merchandise?

2
00:00:08,480 --> 00:00:16,610
Or have you observed how an enthusiastic minister or other speaker has a wide-awake, alert, enthusiastic audience?

3
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:20,850
If you have enthusiasm, those around you will have it too.

4
00:00:21,439 --> 00:00:24,130
But how does one develop enthusiasm?

5
00:00:24,240 --> 00:00:25,969
The basic step is simple.

6
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:27,810
Think enthusiastically.

7
00:00:28,080 --> 00:00:36,050
Build in yourself an optimistic, progressive glow, a feeling that, this is great, and I'm 100% for it.

8
00:00:36,800 --> 00:00:38,449
You are what you think.

9
00:00:38,720 --> 00:00:42,050
Think enthusiasm, and you'll be enthusiastic.

10
00:00:42,240 --> 00:00:47,249
To get high-quality work, be enthusiastic about the job you want done.

11
00:00:47,600 --> 00:00:53,249
Others will catch the enthusiasm you generate, and you'll get first-class performance.

12
00:00:53,760 --> 00:00:59,090
But if, in negative fashion, you cheat that company on expense money, supplies,

13
00:00:59,090 --> 00:01:04,689
and time, and in other little ways, then what can you expect your subordinates to do?

14
00:01:05,040 --> 00:01:10,290
habitually arrive late and leave early, and what do you think the troops will do?

15
00:01:10,880 --> 00:01:18,689
And there is a major incentive for us to think right about our jobs so that our subordinates will think right about their jobs.

16
00:01:19,040 --> 00:01:27,009
Our superiors evaluate us by measuring the quality and quantity of output we get from those reporting to us.

17
00:01:27,840 --> 00:01:29,249
Look at it this way.

18
00:01:29,439 --> 00:01:32,770
Whom would you elevate to division sales manager?

19
00:01:32,880 --> 00:01:41,810
The branch sales manager whose salesmen are doing superior work, or the branch sales manager whose salesmen deliver only average performance?

20
00:01:42,080 --> 00:01:45,810
Or whom would you recommend for promotion to production manager?

21
00:01:46,080 --> 00:01:52,370
The supervisor whose department meets its quota, or the supervisor whose department lags behind?

22
00:01:52,800 --> 00:01:56,850
Here are two suggestions for getting others to do more for you.

23
00:01:56,880 --> 00:01:58,610
1.

24
00:01:58,959 --> 00:02:05,729
Always show positive attitudes toward your job so that your subordinates will pick up right thinking.

25
00:02:05,729 --> 00:02:07,090
2.

26
00:02:07,679 --> 00:02:14,929
As you approach your job each day, ask yourself, am I worthy in every respect of being imitated?

27
00:02:15,120 --> 00:02:20,449
Are all my habits such that I would be glad to see them in my subordinates?

28
00:02:22,720 --> 00:02:26,050
Give yourself a pep talk several times daily.

29
00:02:26,320 --> 00:02:32,770
Several months ago, an automobile salesman told me about the success-producing technique he's developed.

30
00:02:32,880 --> 00:02:33,969
It makes sense.

31
00:02:34,160 --> 00:02:35,249
Listen to it.

32
00:02:35,760 --> 00:02:40,209
A big part of my job, for two hours a day, the salesman explained,

33
00:02:40,320 --> 00:02:44,530
is telephoning prospects to arrange demonstration appointments.

34
00:02:44,880 --> 00:02:49,810
When I first started selling cars three years ago, this was my big problem.

35
00:02:50,320 --> 00:02:55,090
I was shy and afraid, and I know my voice sounded that way on the phone.